1
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:48,190
He wasn't greedy
it's like he knew when to give up

2
00:03:48,493 --> 00:03:51,189
if he'd been more aggressive

3
00:03:51,363 --> 00:03:55,697
he could've been president
maybe even lived longer

4
00:03:56,168 --> 00:04:00,901
with him gone, though
my life is a lot easier

5
00:04:01,206 --> 00:04:05,199
I sometimes feel guilty that
he's not here to share the fun

6
00:04:05,944 --> 00:04:09,311
everything was half measures
his job, the family

7
00:04:10,148 --> 00:04:14,084
well, he had his fun
so cheers

8
00:04:14,352 --> 00:04:16,752
I saw you two going to play golf

9
00:04:17,823 --> 00:04:19,347
did you?

10
00:04:20,192 --> 00:04:23,320
My husband really liked Hiroshi
very much

11
00:04:24,095 --> 00:04:26,188
you were so honest and modest

12
00:04:26,731 --> 00:04:28,255
just a country boy

13
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:32,793
your father died young
didn't he, Hiroshi?

14
00:04:33,572 --> 00:04:37,235
Yes, I was five, so I don't remember
what he looked like

15
00:04:37,709 --> 00:04:41,873
I rather envy you
my father lived to 98 years old

16
00:04:42,113 --> 00:04:44,308
we got sick of the sight of each other

17
00:04:48,753 --> 00:04:51,051
Mitsuru, have you fed them?

18
00:04:51,423 --> 00:04:52,321
Not yet?

19
00:04:52,524 --> 00:04:53,923
You want to feed them with daddy?

20
00:04:55,727 --> 00:04:57,319
I'll help you

21
00:05:04,803 --> 00:05:05,770
excuse us

22
00:05:12,444 --> 00:05:15,971
it's a silly hobby
keeping chickens like that

23
00:05:18,350 --> 00:05:21,148
as he said himself
he's a country boy

24
00:05:39,271 --> 00:05:40,966
Mitsuru, here

25
00:05:48,413 --> 00:05:50,142
let me in there

26
00:05:54,819 --> 00:05:58,380
look, a freshly laid egg

27
00:05:59,691 --> 00:06:03,183
it's spring, that's when they
lay a lot of eggs

28
00:06:03,895 --> 00:06:05,556
little chicks will hatch

29
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:06,956
chicks?

30
00:06:07,132 --> 00:06:11,592
Then they'll grow up and lay more eggs

31
00:06:11,903 --> 00:06:13,996
they're nice and warm

32
00:06:21,580 --> 00:06:24,242
I've never chanted sutras
to hens before

33
00:06:26,551 --> 00:06:28,712
a little souvenir for you

34
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:31,953
they're delicious
not like supermarket eggs

35
00:06:32,857 --> 00:06:34,950
well, thank you very much

36
00:06:35,961 --> 00:06:37,758
I'll wrap them for you

37
00:06:37,963 --> 00:06:38,952
thank you

38
00:06:40,465 --> 00:06:44,595
I've stayed far too long
I really must go now

39
00:06:44,903 --> 00:06:46,768
we appreciate your prayers

40
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:12,621
why don't we sing a song for
father in heaven?

41
00:07:14,299 --> 00:07:19,737
When I first put to sea
as a sailor man

42
00:07:21,806 --> 00:07:26,436
the mast was smashed
and the sails all torn

43
00:07:26,978 --> 00:07:31,711
mighty waves washed over
the wooden deck

44
00:07:32,150 --> 00:07:36,314
but I'll not be troubled
if it's here that I die

45
00:07:36,688 --> 00:07:40,556
awaiting me is my
lovely bride

46
00:07:41,593 --> 00:07:45,085
and my beloved parents
who await me still

47
00:10:01,633 --> 00:10:03,294
more pills?

48
00:10:04,903 --> 00:10:08,395
Do you think I should go and
see a psychiatrist

49
00:10:09,474 --> 00:10:10,736
trouble sleeping again?

50
00:10:11,009 --> 00:10:12,374
No, not really

51
00:10:15,079 --> 00:10:17,172
I dreamed I was pregnant

52
00:10:19,217 --> 00:10:20,149
that's not funny

53
00:10:21,786 --> 00:10:23,686
it was just a dream

54
00:10:25,590 --> 00:10:26,488
good morning

55
00:10:30,595 --> 00:10:32,062
you think too much

56
00:10:38,570 --> 00:10:39,468
I'd better get going

57
00:10:39,871 --> 00:10:41,031
take care

58
00:10:41,873 --> 00:10:43,067
see you later

59
00:10:45,610 --> 00:10:47,339
you're up early today

60
00:10:48,413 --> 00:10:51,610
come on, let's go and see
your father off

61
00:10:57,522 --> 00:11:00,889
it's good buy
trust me, please

62
00:11:02,026 --> 00:11:03,015
I beg your pardon?

63
00:11:03,228 --> 00:11:09,724
Something less risky?
Maybe convertible debentures?

64
00:11:13,004 --> 00:11:14,596
Oh, really?

65
00:11:17,242 --> 00:11:23,408
My sales are way down
I need your business

66
00:11:27,685 --> 00:11:28,845
you could help me out...

67
00:11:29,087 --> 00:11:30,577
I see
certainly

68
00:11:30,822 --> 00:11:33,757
I'll set it up for you
thank you. Bye

69
00:11:39,597 --> 00:11:42,122
I made that man a millionaire!

70
00:11:43,635 --> 00:11:47,799
The buyers are getting a lot smarter

71
00:11:48,873 --> 00:11:53,242
no, our company is losing
their trust

72
00:11:54,712 --> 00:11:58,808
hello?
Nirazaki from Nippo security

73
00:11:59,484 --> 00:12:01,315
yes, I've got an excellent buy for you

74
00:12:08,559 --> 00:12:14,225
Moodys are downgrading us
it'll be in the newspapers soon

75
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:19,067
that's the end of our company

76
00:12:22,807 --> 00:12:25,571
it'll take more than that

77
00:12:28,513 --> 00:12:30,708
are you dreaming?

78
00:12:31,883 --> 00:12:37,082
They're already drafting articles
about our bankruptcy

79
00:12:41,559 --> 00:12:44,460
your brain only works at the office

80
00:12:45,897 --> 00:12:49,162
do you ever talk to outsiders?

81
00:12:53,271 --> 00:12:58,834
No point in competing at a
company that's going down the tubes

82
00:13:01,479 --> 00:13:04,505
I don't think it'll fail

83
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:08,983
you're living the past

84
00:13:09,821 --> 00:13:12,483
even banks are failing

85
00:13:13,491 --> 00:13:18,656
look, we're in the same
financial sector

86
00:13:19,097 --> 00:13:24,763
in this condition, who's going
to buy our recommendations?

87
00:13:25,003 --> 00:13:29,372
Everyone's clawing like crazy
to get out

88
00:13:31,242 --> 00:13:37,010
central bank won't intervene
better start practicing crowd control

89
00:13:45,223 --> 00:13:46,918
how's Mizuho?

90
00:13:47,125 --> 00:13:48,217
What a question

91
00:13:50,561 --> 00:13:56,227
she's from a good family
she relies on you, so get it together

92
00:13:57,068 --> 00:13:59,593
why should you care?

93
00:14:03,474 --> 00:14:05,965
To tell the truth

94
00:14:06,611 --> 00:14:09,011
I've found a new job

95
00:14:13,317 --> 00:14:15,478
that was quick

96
00:14:16,087 --> 00:14:18,248
no, you're just too slow

97
00:14:25,830 --> 00:14:27,525
what about your clients?

98
00:14:28,499 --> 00:14:33,801
In days we'll be out in the street
no time for them

99
00:14:40,044 --> 00:14:42,638
think about your future

100
00:14:43,314 --> 00:14:44,747
no, I really mean it

101
00:15:34,265 --> 00:15:35,960
is that you, Hiroshi?

102
00:15:37,935 --> 00:15:39,266
Is your name Hiroshi?

103
00:15:39,403 --> 00:15:41,394
Yes...
what can I do for you?

104
00:15:41,672 --> 00:15:43,264
I knew it was you!

105
00:15:46,244 --> 00:15:48,405
You remember me?

106
00:15:52,316 --> 00:15:54,409
You don't, do you?

107
00:15:56,587 --> 00:15:58,020
I guess I can't blame you

108
00:15:58,256 --> 00:16:00,952
you were only five at the time

109
00:16:01,626 --> 00:16:04,117
but I can still see traces of
you as a boy

110
00:16:05,696 --> 00:16:12,693
you're looking good

111
00:16:15,706 --> 00:16:20,837
I've been so eager to see you
I really missed you

112
00:16:21,045 --> 00:16:22,706
sorry
I don't recall you

113
00:16:22,914 --> 00:16:24,779
I'm Sasaichi Hamaguchi!

114
00:16:25,583 --> 00:16:27,915
Don't you recognize your own
father's name?

115
00:16:28,152 --> 00:16:29,141
My father?!

116
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:32,211
My father died a long time ago

117
00:16:33,491 --> 00:16:35,322
Kimiyo told you that, eh?

118
00:16:43,801 --> 00:16:47,567
I was wrong to
abandon you like that

119
00:16:48,372 --> 00:16:52,103
I often thought of
coming back to see you

120
00:16:54,478 --> 00:16:56,207
just never found the chance

121
00:16:56,380 --> 00:16:58,814
what was your name again?

122
00:17:02,019 --> 00:17:03,987
Sasaichi Hamaguchi

123
00:17:07,391 --> 00:17:10,883
I remember mother did tell me that

124
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:20,296
I searched everywhere and now
I've found you. Good!

125
00:17:22,506 --> 00:17:24,872
Can you put me up tonight?

126
00:17:25,076 --> 00:17:28,637
Look, it's all so sudden
I can hardly believe it

127
00:17:29,513 --> 00:17:30,844
I don't blame you

128
00:17:31,983 --> 00:17:34,713
I've got so much to tell you
you'll soon come around

129
00:17:34,919 --> 00:17:37,444
let's have a heart to heart

130
00:17:38,956 --> 00:17:44,258
just you and me, son

131
00:17:48,833 --> 00:17:50,164
sure...

132
00:17:58,242 --> 00:18:03,373
it's strange, he was supposed
to have died ages ago

133
00:18:03,848 --> 00:18:07,807
that's what they said when
you got married

134
00:18:09,887 --> 00:18:11,252
I'll go that

135
00:18:11,622 --> 00:18:12,884
I want to hear, too

136
00:18:13,357 --> 00:18:16,622
you were about 5 years old
at the time

137
00:18:16,894 --> 00:18:20,295
my business went bust
and I was heavily in debt

138
00:18:21,899 --> 00:18:26,359
to stop them getting
the money from Kimiyo,

139
00:18:26,604 --> 00:18:28,538
we got a divorce

140
00:18:29,607 --> 00:18:33,839
these days I sell fishing gear
down in Amasaki

141
00:18:34,879 --> 00:18:39,441
as I got older, I began to
worry about you

142
00:18:40,851 --> 00:18:43,945
how did you find out
where I live?

143
00:18:45,656 --> 00:18:50,355
Your mother had told
her parents about you

144
00:18:50,928 --> 00:18:55,160
how you graduated and
married into a good family

145
00:18:55,433 --> 00:18:58,368
I had a private detective
search for you

146
00:18:59,270 --> 00:19:02,569
that was five years ago

147
00:19:03,574 --> 00:19:05,201
five years ago?

148
00:19:06,477 --> 00:19:09,037
So you've know all this time?

149
00:19:11,816 --> 00:19:15,616
I was happy to hear you
were alive and doing well

150
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:19,380
why didn't you contact me then?

151
00:19:20,691 --> 00:19:24,183
Knowing you were doing well
was enough for me

152
00:19:25,830 --> 00:19:27,127
I'll get you a glass

153
00:19:28,899 --> 00:19:29,797
ice, too

154
00:19:30,034 --> 00:19:32,559
so I closed down my shop

155
00:19:33,237 --> 00:19:38,004
I came to Tokyo
I was eager to see you

156
00:19:40,745 --> 00:19:44,977
it'll be here a week
can I stay till then?

157
00:19:46,117 --> 00:19:47,049
Daddy

158
00:19:47,618 --> 00:19:51,179
Mizuho come get him
and you get into bed

159
00:19:51,956 --> 00:19:53,480
got a son, have you?

160
00:19:53,824 --> 00:19:54,756
This is just too much

161
00:20:07,772 --> 00:20:11,264
never thought I'd be sitting
here drinking with my boy

162
00:20:19,817 --> 00:20:20,841
delicious

163
00:20:44,074 --> 00:20:45,871
is he staying the night?

164
00:20:46,844 --> 00:20:51,178
I can hardly throw him
out into the street

165
00:20:55,319 --> 00:20:59,585
is he really your father?
You told me he was dead

166
00:21:01,358 --> 00:21:03,189
that's what I thought

167
00:21:09,967 --> 00:21:11,332
but one thing...

168
00:21:13,504 --> 00:21:18,464
mother sometimes changed her story
after she'd had a drink

169
00:21:21,045 --> 00:21:22,307
what do you mean?

170
00:21:27,251 --> 00:21:29,845
He is your father, isn't he?

171
00:21:33,357 --> 00:21:34,619
I really don't know

172
00:21:37,828 --> 00:21:42,788
you don't know?
Then what should I do?

173
00:21:48,105 --> 00:21:50,005
Again, I don't know

174
00:21:55,012 --> 00:21:58,971
I have trouble comprehending
he's my father

175
00:22:20,838 --> 00:22:22,999
I need time to think it over

176
00:23:17,294 --> 00:23:19,785
I can't believe it!

177
00:23:22,366 --> 00:23:24,391
For me?
Thank you!

178
00:23:24,635 --> 00:23:27,126
Miss me?
Of course I did

179
00:23:27,338 --> 00:23:30,933
it's getting harder to get
a full truckload

180
00:23:31,342 --> 00:23:34,937
of course he's not your father!

181
00:23:36,513 --> 00:23:37,707
Then who is he?

182
00:23:39,717 --> 00:23:43,983
Ignore him
he's just there to sponge off you

183
00:23:44,521 --> 00:23:46,682
my bill
thank you

184
00:23:49,827 --> 00:23:52,955
he'll stay forever if you let him

185
00:23:53,197 --> 00:23:54,664
get rid of him

186
00:24:30,834 --> 00:24:33,894
he's a practical man
not like Hiroshi

187
00:24:35,039 --> 00:24:37,473
is he really Hiroshi's father?

188
00:24:39,343 --> 00:24:42,403
I should ask him to repair
the sliding door

189
00:24:47,851 --> 00:24:50,979
watch out for the thorns

190
00:24:51,355 --> 00:24:53,448
my hands can take it

191
00:24:54,525 --> 00:24:58,359
at this time of year the branches
are very flexible

192
00:25:00,431 --> 00:25:06,063
cut them now and they'll shoot
new branches and buds

193
00:25:08,305 --> 00:25:10,967
bantams, aren't they?

194
00:25:11,341 --> 00:25:13,741
No, they're hens

195
00:25:14,545 --> 00:25:16,240
Hiroshi keeps them?

196
00:25:20,684 --> 00:25:23,278
He hated them when he was a kid

197
00:25:46,210 --> 00:25:49,771
why is he suddenly so eager
to see you now?

198
00:25:51,648 --> 00:25:55,550
I heard he was shacked up
with a woman in Amasaki

199
00:25:56,487 --> 00:25:57,715
you knew all along?

200
00:26:00,824 --> 00:26:02,815
The folks in my hometown...

201
00:26:03,827 --> 00:26:07,388
were kind enough to tell me

202
00:26:11,001 --> 00:26:15,870
so... he really is my father

203
00:26:18,575 --> 00:26:22,443
looks like he believes you're
his son, too

204
00:26:24,181 --> 00:26:25,478
what does that mean?

205
00:26:25,983 --> 00:26:27,644
Just forget it

206
00:26:27,885 --> 00:26:32,083
have nothing to do with him

207
00:26:32,289 --> 00:26:33,881
mother, Shige should leave

208
00:26:37,427 --> 00:26:40,396
you've lost weight
are you eating properly?

209
00:26:40,631 --> 00:26:42,428
Of course I am

210
00:26:43,867 --> 00:26:45,266
wake up!

211
00:26:46,870 --> 00:26:50,328
Shige!
It's time to head out

212
00:26:50,574 --> 00:26:52,098
thanks for reminding me

213
00:26:52,376 --> 00:26:53,570
take care

214
00:26:55,879 --> 00:26:57,369
look...

215
00:26:57,648 --> 00:26:59,741
he was absolutely hopeless

216
00:27:01,051 --> 00:27:04,646
he took half measures
he was a quitter

217
00:27:05,355 --> 00:27:09,121
he started out as a deckhand
on a freighter

218
00:27:10,093 --> 00:27:13,085
then he became an auto-mechanic

219
00:27:13,330 --> 00:27:17,892
after that he borrowed money
to buy a fishing boat

220
00:27:25,375 --> 00:27:29,402
he never stuck to any one thing
for very long

221
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:32,544
he was heavily in debt

222
00:27:32,783 --> 00:27:36,549
he wanted to use my money
so I divorced him

223
00:27:36,887 --> 00:27:38,855
then he went missing

224
00:27:43,093 --> 00:27:46,722
the man was a
loud-mouthed braggart

225
00:27:47,364 --> 00:27:50,527
a woman chaser and
a big spender

226
00:27:51,268 --> 00:27:53,998
no redeeming virtues at all

227
00:27:54,271 --> 00:27:58,503
so you killed him off and
told me he died?

228
00:27:58,775 --> 00:28:00,003
Forget that

229
00:28:00,310 --> 00:28:03,245
don't get involved with him

230
00:28:03,547 --> 00:28:09,042
he'll only create problems with
Mizuho and her mother

231
00:28:11,688 --> 00:28:16,853
but if he is my father
I can't just ignore him

232
00:28:17,561 --> 00:28:21,019
you should have called me first

233
00:28:24,668 --> 00:28:29,765
how's Mitsuru? I really miss him
he must be getting big

234
00:28:32,409 --> 00:28:34,138
hi there, how is it?

235
00:28:34,611 --> 00:28:36,010
Hello little brother

236
00:28:37,414 --> 00:28:39,348
what brings you here?

237
00:28:40,751 --> 00:28:42,116
Want a beer?

238
00:28:42,319 --> 00:28:43,752
No thanks. I must go

239
00:28:43,954 --> 00:28:45,182
two glasses

240
00:28:49,493 --> 00:28:53,987
you really should see more
of your mother

241
00:28:54,598 --> 00:28:56,691
don't leave everything to us

242
00:28:57,367 --> 00:28:59,062
sorry, I'm just so busy

243
00:29:02,739 --> 00:29:03,899
sit down

244
00:29:21,825 --> 00:29:23,793
what's the news at work?

245
00:29:25,295 --> 00:29:28,856
The newspaper say your
company's going under

246
00:29:30,767 --> 00:29:32,394
well...
times are tough

247
00:29:33,337 --> 00:29:38,172
during the bubble economy
you swaggered about

248
00:29:38,475 --> 00:29:41,137
you're not swaggering now

249
00:29:41,411 --> 00:29:44,710
he'll be fine once the economy picks up

250
00:29:47,818 --> 00:29:49,410
okay, I'll see you later

251
00:29:49,987 --> 00:29:54,151
but you don't have to worry, do you?

252
00:29:55,625 --> 00:29:58,856
You married into a wealthy family

253
00:30:00,297 --> 00:30:01,821
right. See you later

254
00:30:03,300 --> 00:30:06,064
get rid of him as soon as possible

255
00:30:06,403 --> 00:30:09,702
if you don't, it'll only lead to problems

256
00:30:13,043 --> 00:30:23,317
begone ye devils!

257
00:30:34,998 --> 00:30:37,728
What did he want?

258
00:30:37,934 --> 00:30:40,027
I've no idea
but it sounded important

259
00:30:40,203 --> 00:30:45,266
why don't you put your foot down?

260
00:30:47,044 --> 00:30:49,740
He should share in taking care of mom

261
00:30:50,013 --> 00:30:53,449
the diner can't last for much longer

262
00:30:53,650 --> 00:30:55,345
not so fast

263
00:30:57,220 --> 00:31:04,353
I'm working on the franchise deal now

264
00:31:51,108 --> 00:31:55,306
begone de devils!

265
00:32:02,185 --> 00:32:05,450
Grandpa!

266
00:32:06,056 --> 00:32:11,221
Are you okay, grandpa?

267
00:32:47,030 --> 00:32:48,827
You must be exhausted

268
00:32:49,766 --> 00:32:52,530
have a drink

269
00:32:56,406 --> 00:32:59,534
stop it, Mitsuru
that's enough

270
00:33:00,644 --> 00:33:04,080
it's over

