sorry for the bother

550
01:08:13,320 --> 01:08:14,947
what a surprise!

551
01:08:15,322 --> 01:08:17,483
Who was that woman?

552
01:08:18,325 --> 01:08:24,161
He's back there again?
How can I ever apologize?

553
01:08:25,366 --> 01:08:27,095
Yes, of course

554
01:08:27,334 --> 01:08:32,294
I'll be there tonight
Alright, see you then

555
01:08:36,644 --> 01:08:41,104
mother, are you going out tonight?

556
01:08:41,315 --> 01:08:43,647
Yes, I have some errands

557
01:08:44,518 --> 01:08:49,421
we wanted to talk to you about
redistributing the property

558
01:08:50,424 --> 01:08:53,086
I haven't changed my mind

559
01:08:53,694 --> 01:08:58,461
it's me who set up and
ran this shop

560
01:08:59,767 --> 01:09:05,501
you can take over when I receive
what we agreed to

561
01:09:06,774 --> 01:09:11,734
then you can change it to a
pinball parlor or a motel

562
01:09:12,046 --> 01:09:13,377
you can do as you please

563
01:09:46,714 --> 01:09:50,582
he certainly has a nerve
that man

564
01:09:52,419 --> 01:09:57,118
I told Hiroshi that he had died

565
01:09:57,324 --> 01:10:01,226
he's only brought trouble
for Mizuho and Hiroshi

566
01:10:01,895 --> 01:10:06,628
to think he was my husband of
30 years ago,

567
01:10:07,568 --> 01:10:10,469
I could sink through the floor

568
01:10:10,904 --> 01:10:11,893
please

569
01:10:14,975 --> 01:10:16,806
hello, Hiroshi

570
01:10:20,881 --> 01:10:22,348
what brings you here?

571
01:10:24,718 --> 01:10:26,652
Leave everything to me

572
01:10:48,509 --> 01:10:53,276
father, if you don't mind

573
01:11:11,732 --> 01:11:13,859
mother wants to talk to you

574
01:11:14,468 --> 01:11:15,730
what?

575
01:11:18,238 --> 01:11:23,642
Are you Kimiyo?
You are, aren't you?

576
01:11:25,712 --> 01:11:31,309
Don't look at me like that

577
01:11:31,718 --> 01:11:36,246
long time no see, Sasaichi

578
01:11:38,492 --> 01:11:41,757
this is a surprise
I'm dumbfounded

579
01:11:43,130 --> 01:11:46,463
you've gotten old

580
01:11:49,603 --> 01:11:55,473
there's something that I must tell you

581
01:11:55,843 --> 01:12:01,008
I realize that you're not happy
with this arrangement

582
01:12:01,782 --> 01:12:06,685
but all I've got left is Hiroshi

583
01:12:07,421 --> 01:12:12,256
he's my only son, he is

584
01:12:12,526 --> 01:12:13,788
I am sorry

585
01:12:15,529 --> 01:12:20,296
but you're really not Hiroshi's father

586
01:12:21,935 --> 01:12:27,567
there's no blood link at all
you're complete strangers

587
01:12:28,142 --> 01:12:30,702
wait...
mother!

588
01:12:31,311 --> 01:12:34,007
But he really isn't your father

589
01:12:35,482 --> 01:12:38,645
Minoru Kataoka is

590
01:12:39,553 --> 01:12:42,283
what did you say?

591
01:12:43,257 --> 01:12:46,192
A year before Hiroshi was born

592
01:12:46,426 --> 01:12:53,059
that tuna fisherman, Kaikichi
asked you to work for him

593
01:12:53,400 --> 01:12:56,597
you went off to Australia
didn't you?

594
01:12:59,139 --> 01:13:04,634
During those 6 months
that you were away...

595
01:13:05,245 --> 01:13:10,114
I fell pregnant with
Minoru's child

596
01:13:13,987 --> 01:13:16,956
I did a good job of fooling you

597
01:13:17,157 --> 01:13:22,356
but the truth is that Hiroshi
is really Minoru's son

598
01:13:23,030 --> 01:13:30,937
there were rumors
you could have heard about it

599
01:13:34,575 --> 01:13:36,202
what does that make me?

600
01:13:36,443 --> 01:13:38,536
You needn't worry

601
01:13:39,012 --> 01:13:45,247
Minoru is a man I longed for
when I was young

602
01:13:46,386 --> 01:13:52,052
so kind, a real hunk and a leader
of the young men's association

603
01:13:52,960 --> 01:13:54,222
so...

604
01:13:55,996 --> 01:13:58,294
...so that's the story

605
01:14:05,239 --> 01:14:10,768
I'm sorry to upset you
but that's what happened

606
01:14:13,914 --> 01:14:16,576
so that's what happened?

607
01:14:19,686 --> 01:14:22,211
So, Minoru is...

608
01:14:26,526 --> 01:14:33,591
my husband passed away
3 years ago

609
01:14:33,934 --> 01:14:36,732
I really have no choice

610
01:14:37,337 --> 01:14:40,067
if you take Hiroshi
what's left for me?

611
01:14:40,307 --> 01:14:43,401
He's all I have left

612
01:14:47,514 --> 01:14:49,141
okay, I understand

613
01:14:51,685 --> 01:14:55,086
well I can't stay here
can I?

614
01:14:57,791 --> 01:14:59,952
Hiroshi, I'm sorry about all this

615
01:15:13,173 --> 01:15:15,073
well, there's no hurry

616
01:15:15,242 --> 01:15:19,144
you can stay longer
we've no objections

617
01:15:19,513 --> 01:15:21,879
now I know the facts
I have to go

618
01:15:28,021 --> 01:15:30,182
you just forget all about me

619
01:15:30,924 --> 01:15:35,520
thanks for everything

620
01:15:47,908 --> 01:15:55,644
father!

621
01:15:57,784 --> 01:16:00,947
Ambulance!
Call an ambulance!

622
01:16:14,735 --> 01:16:16,066
Come in

623
01:16:20,307 --> 01:16:23,174
why did you wait until
he was critical?

624
01:16:23,643 --> 01:16:25,110
Is it that bad?

625
01:16:26,713 --> 01:16:28,977
It's terminal cirrhosis
with extreme complications

626
01:16:30,650 --> 01:16:37,749
if he has another attack
he could die

627
01:16:39,359 --> 01:16:41,327
I doubt he'll pull through

628
01:16:41,995 --> 01:16:43,257
I understand

629
01:16:49,770 --> 01:16:51,101
I appreciate it, doctor

630
01:18:47,754 --> 01:18:50,814
mom, the hen has laid more eggs!

631
01:18:51,458 --> 01:18:52,390
Really?

632
01:18:56,563 --> 01:18:58,861
We'll take them to grandpa

633
01:18:59,132 --> 01:19:00,463
will they make him better?

634
01:19:01,635 --> 01:19:02,431
Yes

635
01:19:02,602 --> 01:19:04,467
really?
Yes, dear

636
01:19:05,872 --> 01:19:07,703
put them in the basket

637
01:19:16,816 --> 01:19:17,783
here

638
01:19:20,620 --> 01:19:22,611
freshly laid
just this morning

639
01:19:26,293 --> 01:19:28,056
put them over there

640
01:19:29,429 --> 01:19:30,225
certainly

641
01:19:33,333 --> 01:19:39,465
I brought some radish relish
you like it, don't you?

642
01:19:40,974 --> 01:19:43,875
And some soup, too

643
01:19:44,311 --> 01:19:46,404
don't worry about me

644
01:19:48,415 --> 01:19:51,282
it wasn't much trouble

645
01:19:51,651 --> 01:19:55,519
grandpa, a picture for you

646
01:19:55,922 --> 01:19:58,186
they're just leftovers

647
01:19:58,458 --> 01:19:59,789
hang it up there

648
01:20:02,262 --> 01:20:04,492
leaving your washing out

649
01:20:07,701 --> 01:20:10,636
I want you to do me a favor

650
01:20:12,572 --> 01:20:13,630
what is it?

651
01:20:16,776 --> 01:20:19,609
I'd like some sake

652
01:20:23,016 --> 01:20:28,010
no, you can't
a small bottle will do

653
01:20:28,421 --> 01:20:30,150
I can't do that

654
01:20:31,825 --> 01:20:37,161
the doctor will be furious and
after all, this is a hospital

655
01:20:41,368 --> 01:20:44,303
so just forget all about drinking!

656
01:20:52,178 --> 01:20:56,478
Even if he isn't your real father
he took care of you as a boy

657
01:20:56,816 --> 01:20:59,683
so let's do what we can for him

658
01:21:01,054 --> 01:21:02,646
but that costs money

659
01:21:04,024 --> 01:21:07,790
I have savings
I can pay the hospital bill

660
01:21:08,995 --> 01:21:11,623
you've never lacked for anything

661
01:21:11,865 --> 01:21:14,561
maybe so
but please

662
01:21:17,437 --> 01:21:19,428
you've never known hardship

663
01:21:34,554 --> 01:21:42,928
morning has broken
dawn has come

664
01:21:43,496 --> 01:21:46,397
no matter what they say
a man needs a drink

665
01:21:48,101 --> 01:21:50,331
that's the truth

666
01:21:50,737 --> 01:21:54,571
hearts bursting with pride...

667
01:21:54,841 --> 01:22:11,122
the pride of men who go to sea

668
01:22:28,174 --> 01:22:33,976
okay, cut it out!
The staff are furious with you

669
01:22:34,481 --> 01:22:38,508
they'll kick you out
if you don't stop now

670
01:22:40,019 --> 01:22:42,180
we'd better go

671
01:22:43,590 --> 01:22:46,650
you take care of yourself

672
01:23:11,518 --> 01:23:12,712
cover up

673
01:23:27,267 --> 01:23:35,800
I was but a lad of fourteen years

674
01:23:37,811 --> 01:23:44,842
when first I put to sea as
a sailor man

675
01:23:45,151 --> 01:23:49,918
the first time our ship cleared the port

676
01:23:52,725 --> 01:23:58,027
the mast was smashed and
the sails all torn

677
01:23:58,431 --> 01:24:04,301
mighty waves washed over
the wooden deck

678
01:24:04,604 --> 01:24:15,776
but I'll not be troubled
if it's here that I die

679
01:24:16,182 --> 01:24:17,979
that song...

680
01:24:20,753 --> 01:24:23,051
it's our song, lad

681
01:24:36,369 --> 01:24:41,466
when first I put to sea as
a sailor man

682
01:24:42,342 --> 01:24:47,370
the mast was smashed and
the sails all torn

683
01:24:47,780 --> 01:24:52,649
mighty waves washed over
the wooden deck

684
01:24:52,952 --> 01:24:57,685
but I'll not be troubled
if it's here that I die

685
01:24:57,991 --> 01:25:02,189
awaiting me is my lovely bride

686
01:25:02,462 --> 01:25:07,593
and my parents
more important to me

687
01:25:08,234 --> 01:25:13,433
Neptune beckons me...

688
01:25:23,116 --> 01:25:27,052
I really am your son after all

689
01:25:32,892 --> 01:25:36,851
as Kimiyo says
I might be infertile

690
01:25:49,442 --> 01:25:57,281
offer up prayers
and make your vows

691
01:25:58,017 --> 01:26:07,653
to Neptune
the king of all seas

692
01:26:08,661 --> 01:26:16,864
mighty Neptune
will you quieten the storm?

693
01:26:17,170 --> 01:26:26,169
For just a little while
for just a little while

694
01:28:33,906 --> 01:28:36,272
I wonder how he is?

695
01:28:37,110 --> 01:28:38,042
Well...

696
01:28:39,712 --> 01:28:44,945
I visited the hospital today
but he was fast asleep

697
01:28:47,854 --> 01:28:49,913
he's like that recently

698
01:28:52,225 --> 01:28:58,027
the man's nuisance whether
he's sick or well

699
01:29:02,301 --> 01:29:03,529
it's too bad

700
01:29:27,293 --> 01:29:28,817
what are you doing?

701
01:29:34,000 --> 01:29:36,662
Shall I make a snack?

702
01:29:38,971 --> 01:29:40,336
Listen...

703
01:29:45,778 --> 01:29:46,904
look...

704
01:29:49,282 --> 01:29:51,216
I must apologize to you

705
01:29:52,185 --> 01:29:53,345
what for?

706
01:29:53,920 --> 01:29:58,016
The company's restructuring plan
was rejected

707
01:30:02,995 --> 01:30:05,964
that means they're bankrupt

708
01:30:12,371 --> 01:30:16,740
you only ever give results

709
01:30:17,743 --> 01:30:19,938
it was all so sudden

710
01:30:26,152 --> 01:30:29,588
you never discuss anything
you never have

711
01:30:30,790 --> 01:30:36,092
you turned your back on
your own father

712
01:30:36,295 --> 01:30:41,995
selfishly thinking
only you've suffered

713
01:30:47,773 --> 01:30:49,866
maybe you're right

714
01:30:52,845 --> 01:30:56,281
did I really enjoy my work?

715
01:30:59,252 --> 01:31:01,982
There'll be no final payment

716
01:31:04,590 --> 01:31:06,990
I don't know what to do

717
01:31:28,414 --> 01:31:30,279
hello, Nirazaki residence

718
01:31:39,191 --> 01:31:40,522
it's the hospital!

719
01:31:41,394 --> 01:31:43,362
Your father's dying!

720
01:31:43,729 --> 01:31:44,923
Take the call

721
01:31:59,111 --> 01:32:02,444
we should've contacted you earlier

722
01:32:06,252 --> 01:32:10,052
I never knew if he wanted to
live or not

723
01:32:24,103 --> 01:32:26,936
my sincere regrets

724
01:33:11,150 --> 01:33:16,281
let's go
let's go home

725
01:33:40,780 --> 01:33:45,479
little chicks!
This is incredible!

726
01:33:49,188 --> 01:33:53,784
He said he would try to hatch them

727
01:33:54,660 --> 01:33:57,060
and he did it!

728
01:33:59,465 --> 01:34:06,598
He didn't eat those eggs
he nurtured them

729
01:34:10,709 --> 01:34:14,304
who would ever have imagined?

730
01:34:34,300 --> 01:34:35,631
Father...

731
01:35:22,781 --> 01:35:25,147
spreading his ashes, how sad

732
01:35:27,553 --> 01:35:31,546
I bet he's happy
he loved a ceremony

733
01:35:32,024 --> 01:35:33,616
I wonder...

734
01:35:34,560 --> 01:35:39,930
I never saw the body
so I keep expecting him to turn up

735
01:35:40,666 --> 01:35:44,124
if he did, would you insure him again?

736
01:35:44,470 --> 01:35:47,030
Don't say that!
I was good to him

737
01:35:47,373 --> 01:35:49,000
it was such a short time...

738
01:35:50,976 --> 01:35:53,410
you seem to be getting younger

739
01:35:57,850 --> 01:36:00,216
really?
Do you think so?

740
01:36:00,886 --> 01:36:02,751
Shall we begin?

741
01:36:02,922 --> 01:36:04,685
I suppose we must

742
01:36:16,969 --> 01:36:19,563
will normal funerary prayers do?

743
01:36:19,872 --> 01:36:21,499
Anything, I suppose

744
01:36:21,740 --> 01:36:26,268
great god of compassion...

745
01:36:30,316 --> 01:36:37,119
ashes to ashes
dust to dust

746
01:37:07,386 --> 01:37:09,786
doesn't Hiroshi take after him?

747
01:37:12,691 --> 01:37:14,659
You lied, didn't you?

748
01:37:21,533 --> 01:37:23,364
I'll keep a piece of him

749
01:37:31,276 --> 01:37:33,335
which bone was it?

750
01:37:41,620 --> 01:37:44,521
I'll have to find a new job

751
01:37:46,859 --> 01:37:52,161
don't worry
life will go on

752
01:37:56,969 --> 01:37:59,335
you know, I'm quite strong

753
01:38:02,841 --> 01:38:07,039
even so
it's a long haul...

754
01:38:14,753 --> 01:38:18,189
Mitsuru!
You've got a strong mother!
